e Vaux VI于大约1170年出生在英国諾圖波藍德吉爾曼德时，他的父亲Ranulf de Vaux27岁，母亲Alicia of Gilsland22岁。他于大约1189年与Maud de Vaux of Cumberland在英国波藍德结婚。他们至少是2个儿子和1个女儿的父母。他去世于1235年享年66岁。"},"hr":{"about 1170–1235":"oko 1170.–1235.","1170–1235":"1170–1235.","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"preminula","1175–Female":"1175–preminula","1177–Female":"1177–preminula","1190–1240":"1190.–1240","1197–Male":"1197–preminuo","1207–1269":"1207.–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199.","1150–Female":"1150–preminula","1190":"1190.","about 1170":"oko 1170.","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1235":"1235.","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1145":"1145","1199":"1199.","1177":"1177","about 1189":"oko 1189.","about 1197":"oko 1197.","1207":"1207.","Freston, Suffolk, England":"Freston, Suffolk, England","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, England","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"cs":{"about 1170–1235":"okolo 1170–1235","1170–1235":"1170–1235","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"Zesnulá","1175–Female":"1175–Zesnulá","1177–Female":"1177–Zesnulá","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1197–Male":"1197–Zesnulý","1207–1269":"1207–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199","1150–Female":"1150–Zesnulá","1190":"1190","about 1170":"okolo 1170","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1177":"1177","about 1189":"okolo 1189","about 1197":"okolo 1197","1207":"1207","Freston, Suffolk, England":"Freston, Suffolk, Anglie","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, Anglie","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumberland, Anglie","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1170–1235":"omkring 1170–1235","1170–1235":"1170–1235","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"Afdød","1175–Female":"1175–Afdød","1177–Female":"1177–Afdød","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1197–Male":"1197–Afdød","1207–1269":"1207–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199","1150–Female":"1150–Afdød","1190":"1190","about 1170":"omkring 1170","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1177":"1177","about 1189":"omkring 1189","about 1197":"omkring 1197","1207":"1207","Freston, Suffolk, England":"Freston, Suffolk, England","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, England","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumbraland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumbraland, England"},"nl":{"about 1170–1235":"circa 1170–1235","1170–1235":"1170–1235","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"Overleden","1175–Female":"1175–Overleden","1177–Female":"1177–Overleden","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1197–Male":"1197–Overleden","1207–1269":"1207–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199","1150–Female":"1150–Overleden","1190":"1190","about 1170":"circa 1170","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1177":"1177","about 1189":"circa 1189","about 1197":"circa 1197","1207":"1207","Freston, Suffolk, England":"Freston, Suffolk, England","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, England","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"en":{"about 1170–1235":"about 1170–1235","1170–1235":"1170–1235","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"Deceased","1175–Female":"1175–Deceased","1177–Female":"1177–Deceased","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1197–Male":"1197–Deceased","1207–1269":"1207–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199","1150–Female":"1150–Deceased","1190":"1190","about 1170":"about 1170","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1177":"1177","about 1189":"about 1189","about 1197":"about 1197","1207":"1207","Freston, Suffolk, England":"Freston, Suffolk, England","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, England","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Vaux","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin) and French: habitational name from any of various places in northern France called Vaux, from the Old French plural of <i>val</i> ‘valley’. Compare English   Vause   and French   Devaux  .","History: Richard Vaux (1749–90) emigrated from Sussex, England, to Philadelphia, PA, in early youth. Calvert Vaux, landscape architect, emigrated from London, England, to America in 1850 and designed several major US parks, including Central Park in New York City (with Frederick Olmstead). — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its variant <i>Veaux</i> and altered form   Devoe  ) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."],"variants":[{"name":"Vause","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire):","of Norman origin, a habitational name from Vaux (see   Vaux  ), a common French placename, singular and plural of <i>val</i> ‘valley’, the plural form being Latinized in surnames as <i>de Vallibus</i>. Norman lords with this surname are recorded in 12th- and early 13th-century records in Cumberland (Irthington), Devon (Farwood, in Colyton), East Yorkshire (Warter), Essex (Belchamp), and Leicestershire (Belvoir). Compare   Vale  .","nickname perhaps from Middle English <i>fals</i>, <i>faus</i>, <i>vaus</i> (Old French <i>fals</i>, <i>faus</i>, Old English <i>fals</i>) ‘deceitful, disloyal, dishonest, mendacious’, but it is more likely the name arises from 1, with the common Anglo-Norman French substitution of <i>le</i> for <i>de</i> in their surname."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Vaux VI was born about 1170, in Gilsland, Northumberland, England, his father, Ranulf de Vaux, was 27 and his mother, Alicia of Gilsland, was 22. He married Maud de Vaux of Cumberland about 1189, in Cumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1235, at the age of 66."},"et":{"about 1170–1235":"umbes 1170–1235","1170–1235":"1170–1235","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1177–Female":"1177–Surnud","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1197–Male":"1197–Surnud","1207–1269":"1207–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1197":"1197","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1215":"1215","1269":"1269","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1177":"1177","about 1189":"umbes 1189","about 1197":"umbes 1197","1207":"1207","Freston, Suffolk, England":"Freston, Suffolk, England","Gilsland, Northumberland, England":"Gilsland, Northumberland, England","Irthington, Cumberland, England":"Irthington, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"about 1170–1235":"noin 1170–1235","1170–1235":"1170–1235","–1212":"–1212","–Female":"Kuollut","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1177–Female":"1177–Kuollut","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1197–Male":"1197–Kuollut","1207–1269":"1207–1269","1145–1199":"1145–1199","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1170":"noin 1170",